    "question": "What is the observed significance level (p-value) for the test of the mean filling weight in Examples 7.3 and 7.5?"
  },
  "output": {
    "answer": "We are testing $H_0: \\mu=12$ ounces versus $H_{\\mathrm{a}}: \\mu \\neq 12$ ounces. The observed value of the test statistic in Example 7.5 was $z=-2.91$, and any value of $z$ less than -2.91 or greater than 2.91 (because this is a two-tailed test) would be even more contradictory to $H_0$. Therefore, the observed significance level for the test is $$ p \\text{-value }=P(z<-2.91 \\text{ or } z>2.91)=P(|z|>2.91) $$."
  },
